[SN]TITLE[SN]
Police charge 15-year-old over Galashiels abattoir fire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 15-year-old boy has been charged with causing a deliberate fire in Galashiels.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
It follows a police investigation into a blaze at a former abattoir in Winston Road on 4 March.
Nobody was hurt in the incident but the building was extensively damaged and Winston Road was closed for several hours.
Police said the teenager was arrested on 25 March and a report was sent to the procurator fiscal.
